abstract: Former Afghan lawmaker Semin Barakzai ends her hunger strike of more than two weeks over her removal from office after appeal from one of country's most revere elders Subghatullah Mujaddedi.
snippet: Semin Barakzai, a former Afghan lawmaker, ended a hunger strike of more than two weeks over her removal from office after an appeal from one of the country’s most revered elders.
lead_paragraph: Semin Barakzai, a former Afghan lawmaker, ended a hunger strike of more than two weeks over her removal from office after an appeal from one of the country’s most revered elders.

headline.main: Afghanistan: Ex-Lawmaker Ends Her Hunger Strike
